WHAT THIS PART DOES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Part B is the PRODUCTION phase. You receive the approved plan from Part A and
write situation-based image prompts for a specific chunk of scenes.

Part B does NOT re-read the transcript from scratch.
Part B does NOT re-classify beats or re-plan splits.
Part B FOLLOWS the approved plan EXACTLY.

HOW THE CHUNK SYSTEM WORKS:
  You run Part B multiple times — once per chunk:
  → B1: Scene 1 → Scene 50
  → B2: Scene 46 → Scene 100   (5-scene overlap with B1)
  → B3: Scene 96 → Scene [end]  (5-scene overlap with B2)

  Why overlap? Because the last 5 scenes of one chunk are regenerated
  with fresh context at the start of the next chunk. You compare both
  versions and keep the better one. This prevents quality drops at
  chunk boundaries.

  Why chunks? The v4.0 monolithic prompt tried to generate 100-150+
  image prompts in one go. After scene 40+, context overloaded and
  quality drifted. Chunks keep the AI context fresh every 50 scenes.

