CHUNK OVERLAP INSTRUCTIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

When running B2 (scenes 46-100):
  - Scenes 46-50 are REGENERATED with fresh context
  - User compares B1's scenes 46-50 with B2's scenes 46-50
  - User keeps the better version for the final combined output
  - This ensures visual continuity is not broken at the chunk boundary

When running B3 (scenes 96-end):
  - Scenes 96-100 are REGENERATED with fresh context
  - User compares B2's scenes 96-100 with B3's scenes 96-100
  - User keeps the better version for the final combined output

WHY OVERLAP WORKS:
  At the end of B1, the AI is at the edge of its context window.
  The last few scenes may be slightly weaker due to context fatigue.
  By regenerating them at the START of B2 (when context is fresh),
  those scenes get full quality attention. The user then compares
  and picks the best version — no quality loss at boundaries.

