RULE 1: Follow the approved plan EXACTLY.
        Do NOT reclassify beats. Do NOT change split counts.
        Do NOT change the sub-beat descriptions from the plan.

RULE 2: Every image prompt = ACTUAL SITUATION (not abstract/symbolic).

RULE 3: No character description in any prompt.
        Reference image handles character. Every prompt starts with the situation.

RULE 4: Prompt structure: [Situation] — [Emotional State] — [Environment] — [Atmosphere]

RULE 5: Keep prompts simple: 2-4 sentences max.
        Simple, clear prompts produce better images.

RULE 6: Floating text allowed: 2-5 words, internal thoughts only.
        Only when it adds emotional clarity.

RULE 7: Use timestamps from the gap-audited plan (Part A Step 6).
        These may differ from raw transcript timestamps — the plan's versions absorb gaps.

RULE 8: Apply emotional timing from the Emotional Timing Map (Part A Step 3).
        Image starts 1-2 words before the emotional word — use the mapped timestamps.

RULE 9: Follow the rhythm pattern from the plan.
        ⚡⚡⚡🔄⚡⚡🫁⚡⚡⚡ — not all fast, not all slow.

RULE 10: No two consecutive scenes should look visually similar.

RULE 11: Same emotion shown through DIFFERENT situations each time.

RULE 12: Output BOTH tables: the 4-column table AND the automation list.
         Both are REQUIRED. Never skip either.

RULE 13: Automation list prompts IDENTICAL to table prompts — word for word.

RULE 14: Automation list has ZERO extra content.
         JUST: number + period + space + "Scene" + space + number + space + prompt.

RULE 15: For overlap scenes (B2: 46-50, B3: 96-100), write them fresh —
         do not copy from previous chunk. Let user compare and choose.

RULE 16: If approved plan is not provided, ASK. Do not proceed.

RULE 17: Do NOT skip any scenes in the assigned range.

